                  <strong>Pay frequency:</strong> Choose how often the employee
                  is paid (weekly, bi‑weekly, semi‑monthly, monthly, or
                  annually).
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>2. Enter earnings</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Salary mode:</strong> Enter the annual salary and any
                  bonus or commission for this paycheck.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Hourly mode:</strong> Enter hourly rate, regular
                  hours, overtime hours, and the overtime multiplier (for
                  example 1.5× for “time and a half”).
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Other taxable pay:</strong> Include taxable
                  allowances, tips, or shift differentials.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>3. Add taxes and deductions</h3>
              <p>In many systems, payroll deductions fall into three groups:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Income tax:</strong> National, state/provincial, or
                  local income tax withheld from the employee.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Social security / pension:</strong> Contributions to
                  public pension, social insurance, or mandatory retirement
                  plans.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Other mandatory taxes:</strong> For example,
                  unemployment insurance, health contributions, or local payroll
                  levies.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p>You can also enter:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Pre‑tax deductions:</strong> Retirement contributions,
                  cafeteria plan, or other amounts that reduce taxable income.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Post‑tax deductions:</strong> Health insurance
                  premiums, union dues, wage garnishments, etc.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>4. (Optional) Estimate employer payroll costs</h3>
              <p>
                Toggle on <strong>Employer payroll costs</strong> to estimate
                what the employee really costs the company:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Employer payroll taxes:</strong> Employer side of
                  social security, Medicare, unemployment, etc.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Benefits:</strong> Employer‑paid health insurance,
                  retirement match, allowances.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Other employer costs:</strong> Workers’ compensation,
                  payroll processing fees, etc.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h2>Formulas used by the calculator</h2>

              <div class="formula-box">
                <p><strong>1. Gross pay per paycheck</strong></p>
                <p>Salary mode:</p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Gross} = \frac{\text{Annual salary}}{\text{Pay
                  periods per year}} + \text{Bonus} + \text{Other taxable} \]
                </p>
                <p>Hourly mode:</p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Regular pay} = \text{Hourly rate} \times
                  \text{Regular hours} \]
                </p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Overtime pay} = \text{Hourly rate} \times
                  \text{Overtime hours} \times \text{Overtime multiplier} \]
                </p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Gross} = \text{Regular pay} + \text{Overtime pay} +
                  \text{Bonus} + \text{Other taxable} \]
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="formula-box">
                <p><strong>2. Taxable income</strong></p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Taxable income} = \max\bigl(0,\ \text{Gross} -
                  \text{Pre‑tax deductions}\bigr) \]
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="formula-box">
                <p><strong>3. Taxes and net pay</strong></p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Income tax} = \text{Taxable income} \times
                  \frac{\text{Income tax rate}}{100} \]
                </p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Social / pension} = \text{Taxable income} \times
                  \frac{\text{Social rate}}{100} \]
                </p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Other taxes} = \text{Taxable income} \times
                  \frac{\text{Other tax rate}}{100} \]
                </p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Net pay} = \text{Gross} - \text{Pre‑tax deductions} -
                  \text{Income tax} - \text{Social / pension} - \text{Other
                  taxes} - \text{Post‑tax deductions} \]
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="formula-box">
                <p><strong>4. Employer cost</strong></p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Employer extras} = \text{Gross} \times
                  \frac{\text{Employer tax rate} + \text{Benefits rate} +
                  \text{Other employer rate}}{100} \]
                </p>
                <p>
                  \[ \text{Employer cost} = \text{Gross} + \text{Employer
                  extras} \]
                </p>
              </div>

              <h2>Limitations and tips</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  This tool uses <strong>flat percentage rates</strong>. Real
                  payroll systems often use progressive tax brackets,
                  thresholds, and caps.
                </li>
                <li>
                  For accurate U.S. federal and state withholding, use our
                  <a href="https://calcdomain.com/us-federal-taxes"
                    >U.S. tax calculators</a
                  >
                  and combine them with this tool if needed.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Always verify results against your official payroll software
                  or government calculators before running live payroll.
                </li>
              </ul>
